The paper deals with unsupervised discovery of acoustic tokens from audio corpora, which is a problem in speech processing and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound), which deals with speech and audio processing. The paper also uses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for learning the mapping between cluster sequences and unknown phoneme sequences, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves learning vector representations for acoustic tokens, which is a problem in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves unsupervised phoneme recognition, which is a problem in artificial intelligence and falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
